Date: 13/4/1920
Source: Otautau Standard & Wallace County Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: At Friday's meeting of the Olautau Saleyards Company, Mr G. A. Burnett urged the necessity of a stock bridge over the Otautau River, and stressed the importance of keeping this need before the Town Board and others interested. .. Traffic was becoming greater and the speed accelerated, and some day there would be a serious accident unless provision was made to cope with the stock traffic independently of the present bridge.
